In the restaurant scene, Basquiat makes friends with **Andy Warhol and Bruno (the art dealer)** after selling them two of his postcards.

This moment marks his entry into the high-profile art world, bridging his street-art roots with the elite gallery scene.

The interaction highlights Basquiat’s growing influence and the beginning of his complex relationship with Warhol. \boxed{\text{Andy Warhol and Bruno}}
